reporting-org.narrative: The federal government of the United States

title.narrative: Revenue Administration and Revenue Policy - Tanzania

description.narrative: Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation – the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.

This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes Enhancing the effectiveness of audits of businesses in telecommunications, tourism, construction and financial instruments; Ensuring that progress made by the Tanzania Revenue Authority in the audit of transfer pricing issues on multinational enterprises continues; Expanding the capabilities of the Tax Investigations Department in deterring and combating tax fraud; Assisting with issues that arise in the acquisition and deployment of the New Integrated Domestic Revenue System (IDRAS); and, developing TRA’s effectiveness in tax administration for the oil and gas industry..
